---
import CTAButton from "./CTAButton.astro";

const formatCards = [
  {
    title: "Courses can be completed asynchronously",
    body: "Students do not need to be in Boulder and do not need to attend regularly scheduled live class meetings. Course materials, assignments, projects, and discussions are designed so students can work through them online while following course deadlines."
  },
  {
    title: "Office hours are live on Zoom",
    body: "Each 3- or 4-credit course has two hours of live instructor office hours each week. These are usually split so one hour is offered during the day and one hour is offered in the evening to help accommodate different schedules."
  },
  {
    title: "Some testing happens on specific days",
    body: "Some courses may schedule tests on particular days. In general, those testing windows are open for the day rather than tied to one short class period."
  }
];

const toolCards = [
  {
    name: "Canvas",
    body: "Canvas is the main course site. Students use it for course materials, announcements, assignments, grades, and course organization."
  },
  {
    name: "Zoom",
    body: "Zoom is used for live office hours and other live course meetings when they are offered."
  },
  {
    name: "Piazza",
    body: "Piazza is used for classroom discussion, required participation in many courses, questions, clarifications, and student-student interaction."
  },
  {
    name: "GitHub",
    body: "GitHub is commonly used for programming work, repositories, version control, and some course submissions."
  },
  {
    name: "Gradescope",
    body: "Gradescope is used in some courses for submitting and grading assignments, quizzes, exams, or programming work."
  }
];

const discussionCards = [
  {
    title: "Required participation in many courses",
    body: "Most CSPB courses require Piazza participation. That participation is not just a box to check. It is part of how students stay engaged with the course and with each other."
  },
  {
    title: "Student-instructor interaction",
    body: "Piazza gives students a place to ask clarifying questions, get help from course staff, and see answers to questions other students are asking."
  },
  {
    title: "Student-student interaction",
    body: "The forums also support substantial student-student interaction. Students compare approaches, explain ideas, help each other debug, and learn from the way other people are thinking about the same problem."
  },
  {
    title: "Time to reflect and compose",
    body: "Because discussion is asynchronous, students have time to reflect, compose meaningful questions, write useful replies, and participate even when their schedules differ."
  }
];

const successItems = [
  {
    title: "Start technical work early",
    body: "Programming assignments and debugging rarely go well when started at the last minute. Successful students usually begin early enough to get stuck, ask questions, and revise."
  },
  {
    title: "Use office hours and discussion boards",
    body: "Online does not mean unsupported. Students should use office hours, Piazza, course staff, and peer discussion when they need help."
  },
  {
    title: "Create a weekly routine",
    body: "The program is flexible, but it is not structure-free. Students need a regular rhythm for lectures, readings, assignments, projects, studying, and communication."
  },
  {
    title: "Expect real collaboration",
    body: "Some courses require team work. Students should be ready to coordinate online, use shared tools, communicate clearly, and contribute to group projects."
  }
];

const workflowSteps = [
  "Check Canvas for weekly materials, due dates, and announcements.",
  "Work through lectures, readings, examples, and course notes.",
  "Participate in Piazza discussions, including required discussion participation in many courses.",
  "Attend Zoom office hours when live help would be useful.",
  "Use GitHub when a course requires repositories or version-control workflows.",
  "Submit work through Canvas, GitHub, Gradescope, or other course-specific tools.",
  "Keep track of exams, project deadlines, team commitments, and grading feedback."
];
---

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">Online format</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">CSPB is online, structured, and built for remote students</h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      The Computer Science Post-Baccalaureate Program (CSPB) can be completed online. Students work through course materials, assignments, projects, discussions, assessments, and deadlines remotely. The format is flexible, but the courses are still real CU Boulder courses with structure, expectations, and regular interaction with course staff.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="auto-grid">
    {formatCards.map((card) => (
      <article class="card card-pad">
        <h3 class="heading-md">{card.title}</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">{card.body}</p>
      </article>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card card-pad">
  <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_0.95fr] lg:items-start">
    <div>
      <p class="kicker">What asynchronous means here</p>
      <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">Flexible does not mean disconnected</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        CSPB courses can be completed asynchronously, which means students can usually decide when during the week they work through course materials and complete assignments. That flexibility is one of the reasons the program works for many students who are working, parenting, relocating, or living outside Colorado.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        But asynchronous does not mean self-paced in the sense of doing everything whenever. Courses have deadlines. Projects have milestones. Some tests have defined testing days. Students need to keep up with the course schedule and ask for help before small problems become large ones.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-[1.25rem] bg-neutral-950 p-5 text-white">
      <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#cfb87c]">Online</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm font-bold leading-6 text-white/80">
        No regular in-person class meetings are required for CSPB coursework.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xs leading-5 text-white/60">
        Live office hours are available through Zoom, and course deadlines still apply.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">Course discussion</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">Piazza discussions are a central part of many courses</h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      Most CSPB courses require participation in Piazza. Those course discussions are often among the most valuable parts of the program because they support both student-instructor interaction and substantial student-student interaction.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="auto-grid">
    {discussionCards.map((card) => (
      <article class="card card-pad">
        <h3 class="heading-md">{card.title}</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">{card.body}</p>
      </article>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">Course tools</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">The main tools students should expect</h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      Different courses may use different combinations of tools, but these are the common systems students should expect to see across the program.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="auto-grid">
    {toolCards.map((tool) => (
      <article class="card card-pad">
        <h3 class="heading-md">{tool.name}</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">{tool.body}</p>
      </article>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">Typical workflow</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">What a course week may involve</h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      The details vary by course, but an online course week usually includes a mix of course materials, technical work, communication, and deadlines.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card card-pad">
    <ol class="space-y-3">
      {workflowSteps.map((step, index) => (
        <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
          <span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-neutral-950 text-xs font-black text-[#cfb87c]">{index + 1}</span>
          <span>{step}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">How students succeed online</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">The format works best when students stay engaged</h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      Online learning gives students flexibility. It also puts more responsibility on students to plan, communicate, and keep moving.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="auto-grid">
    {successItems.map((item) => (
      <article class="card card-pad">
        <h3 class="heading-md">{item.title}</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">{item.body}</p>
      </article>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card card-pad">
  <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.15fr_0.85fr] lg:items-start">
    <div>
      <p class="kicker">Connected online community</p>
      <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">Online does not mean isolated</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Some CSPB courses require team work. Students may collaborate on projects, use GitHub or other shared tools, coordinate meeting times, divide tasks, review each other’s work, and practice communication habits that are common in professional software development.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Students also connect beyond individual courses. CSPB has a very active student-led Discord community where students ask questions, share advice, coordinate informally, and support each other through the program.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-[1.25rem] border border-neutral-200 bg-neutral-50 p-5">
      <p class="kicker">Professional practice</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-bold leading-6 text-neutral-700">
        Remote communication, version control, documentation, team coordination, and community participation are part of modern software work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card card-pad border-l-4 border-l-[#cfb87c]">
  <p class="kicker">Next steps</p>
  <h2 class="heading-md mt-2">Compare the format with your goals and schedule</h2>
  <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
    The online format is a major strength of CSPB, especially for students who need to study from a distance or balance school with work and other responsibilities. The next step is to compare the format with the curriculum, admissions requirements, and your own learning habits.
  </p>
  <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
    <CTAButton href="/modules/is-cspb-right-for-me/" label="Check program fit" variant="dark" />
    <CTAButton href="/modules/curriculum/" label="Review curriculum" variant="secondary" />
    <CTAButton href="/modules/student-support/" label="Review student support" variant="secondary" />
  </div>
</section>
